   – Ellicott, MD        </p>    </li></ul><p>    Landmarks</p><p>    Ellicott City has a fantastic location and history to it, allowing for plenty of exploration and adventuring through the local area. Whether it is    historical buildings, festivities or any kind of other local attraction, you can find plenty to explore in Ellicott City. The area is expansive in parks,    landmarks and all sorts of beauty to enjoy. You will find a lot of history and honor in the area, that is certain.</p><ul>    <li>        <p>            Historic Ellicott City – 8334 Main St – (410) 461-6908        </p>    </li>    <li>        <p>            Symphony Woods – 10300 Hickory Ridge Rd – (866) 216-6630        </p>    </li>    <li>        <p>            Hell House – 4 Ichester Rd        </p>    </li>    <li>        <p>            Friends of P F I at Mt Ida – Ellicott City, MD – (410) 465-8500        </p>    </li></ul><p>    Conclusion</p><p>    <a name="_GoBack"></a>    Ellicott City is a fantastic place to really enjoy the affluent side of Howard County. The city is an absolute gem, not just for its looks, but for all the    amenities it offers. Whether it is great shopping, an active nightlife, beautiful and natural scenery or the delicious slew of restaurants all adds up into    one great experience to be had. The city offers plenty in the way of great school systems and career opportunities, so raising a family in Ellicott City is    a no-brainer. It is also a fantastic place to retire, or just to visit if you are in the area. No matter the reason, Ellicott City should be high on your    list of places to see.</p>
